channel.title: I have issues playing RSPS's [READ]
channel.description:
Hey guys, whenever I want to play a new or different RSPS, it always seems to fail loading, I can basically only play the older Delta servers which you rarely find these days. Most servers tend to load to 80% and then I can't play them.
The fuck? >.<

item.title: I have issues playing RSPS's [READ]
item.dc:creator: @frostyboy07 frostyboy07
item.description:
@frostyboy07 wrote:

[quote=“ultimatepkvillage, post:9, topic:432924”][quote author=frostyboy07 link=topic=535634.msg3920137#msg3920137 date=1329621959]

try a disk cleanup or delete cookies from the cookies folder

Where is the cookies folder? Ahaha…
[/quote]

Im guessing your on windows 7
Start Button
Go to Documents
Click the Organize Button
Folder and Search Options
View Tab
Uncheck the box that says [] Hide operating system files (Recommended)
it will prompt you with a screen if you really want to do it choose yes or whatever it says

Go to start button
then go to login user you are on (should be above documents)
Find App Data folder (click it)
Next click Roaming folder
Then Microsoft Folder
Windows Folder
Cookies Folder
Then if there is any text files in that folder delete them. And there is also a Folder in the cookies folder called Low check in that folder too.[/quote]

Nah’ not Windows 7, but I found it anyways and deleted all the cookies, havn’t tried a server since, will now though.

Read full topic

Folder and Search Options
View Tab
Uncheck the box that says [] Hide operating system files (Recommended)
it will prompt you with a screen if you really want to do it choose yes or whatever it says

Go to start button
then go to login user you are on (should be above documents)
Find App Data folder (click it)
Next click Roaming folder
Then Microsoft Folder
Windows Folder
Cookies Folder
Then if there is any text files in that folder delete them. And there is also a Folder in the cookies folder called Low check in that folder too.
